OL,6,F"This meant that the panel's decision
OL,7,Fwas provisional and that either Mr
OL,8,FPitchfork or the Secretary of State
OL,9,Fcould make an application for
OL,10,Freconsideration on the grounds that
OL,11,Fthe decision not to release Mr
OL,12,FPitchfork had been irrational,
OL,13,Fprocedurally unfair and/or there had
OL,14,Fbeen an error of law.
OL,16,F"Mr Pitchfork made an application for
OL,17,Freconsideration in December 2023 and
OL,18,Fthis was considered and granted by a
OL,19,Freconsideration member of the Parole
OL,20,FBoard in February 2024.
