OL,4,CPitchfork to face fresh parole hearing
OL,6,F"Release can only be directed by the
OL,7,FParole Board if the new panel is
OL,8,Fsatisfied that it is no longer
OL,9,Fnecessary for the protection of the
OL,10,Fpublic that Mr Pitchfork remain
OL,11,Fconfined in prison. Mr Pitchfork has,
OL,12,Fand will continue to, remain in prison
OL,13,Funtil this case has fully concluded."
OL,15,FA Ministry of Justice spokeswoman
OL,16,Fsaid: "Our heartfelt sympathies remain
OL,17,Fwith the families of Lynda Mann and
OL,18,FDawn Ashworth at this difficult time."
